<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-20T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="1409" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1409">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.4016/101</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                            <gloss type="to">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-20T20:00:00+02:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 20, 1915, 8 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 23, 9.15 a.
                                m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>950. Your 955. German Ambassador’s protest has not improved conditions in
                            the interior. Instructions from German Government to their Ambassador to
                            demand from the Sublime Porte that these horrible deportations cease and
                            all possible reparation be promptly made may, with other influences now
                            being exerted, improve the situation. Bulgarians have made strong
                            representations.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_MH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgenthau</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>